1H and 13C NMR data given in Table 1
and Section 5 are in full agreement with the proposed structures 1–14 (Fig. 2
).

In the series of Z-izomers of C-5 alkynyl 1-[4′-(N-phthalimido)-2′-butenyl] pyrimidine derivatives 1–7, compounds containing a hexynyl (1), octynyl (2) and p-butylphenylethynyl (6) side chain at C-5 exhibited moderate cytostatic effects against all evaluated cell lines, particularly against hepatocellular carcinoma (Hep G2; IC50
 = 16.6–40.2 μM) (Fig. 5
). However, these compounds were also cytotoxic against normal human fibroblasts (WI 38; IC50
 = 16.7–49 μM) (Fig. 6
).
